1
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:58,517
{\an8}INSURANCE PAYOUT STATEMENT

2
00:00:59,935 --> 00:01:02,313
You knew your parents
had life insurance, didn't you?

3
00:01:03,981 --> 00:01:06,358
Han Seol-ah, you were
the only survivor at the scene.

4
00:01:09,445 --> 00:01:10,821
Even if no one else knows…

5
00:01:12,865 --> 00:01:13,949
you know the truth.

6
00:01:17,661 --> 00:01:19,163
Who started the fire?

7
00:01:23,918 --> 00:01:25,211
It can't be.

8
00:01:26,796 --> 00:01:27,797
That's right.

9
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:33,803
I did it.

10
00:01:36,347 --> 00:01:37,556
I killed them.

11
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:52,613
[sighs]

12
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:22,518
You have to tell me exactly what happened.

13
00:02:23,018 --> 00:02:24,520
I killed my parents

14
00:02:25,437 --> 00:02:27,064
to collect the insurance payout.

15
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:28,941
[sighs]

16
00:02:29,942 --> 00:02:31,819
What? Isn't that enough?

17
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:35,322
I had those men take out insurance
but my plan failed.

18
00:02:35,406 --> 00:02:38,075
- I killed them all.
- Did you actually do it?

19
00:02:39,368 --> 00:02:41,078
That's what you wanted to hear.
Am I wrong?

20
00:02:41,996 --> 00:02:43,205
Tell me the truth.

21
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:46,834
The truth?

22
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:51,755
I've always spoken the truth.

23
00:02:53,841 --> 00:02:56,927
You're the one who refuses to believe it.

24
00:03:09,982 --> 00:03:11,066
[sighs]

25
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,081
[Seol-ah] <i>I wonder.</i>

26
00:03:26,874 --> 00:03:29,084
<i>If your secret came out</i>
<i>for the whole world to see…</i>

27
00:03:29,168 --> 00:03:30,419
SIU INVESTIGATOR CHA WOO-SEOK

28
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:32,087
<i>…would you still be this graceful?</i>

29
00:03:33,047 --> 00:03:35,466
How long are you going
to keep defending Ms. Han?

30
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:39,553
How long?
I can't show my face in front of the team.

31
00:03:39,637 --> 00:03:41,347
[Chair Kim] But she's invaluable
to me to me.

32
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:45,392
If there's darkness,
there has to be light to keep the balance.

33
00:03:46,352 --> 00:03:47,686
Ma'am.

34
00:03:47,770 --> 00:03:50,522
I heard something
that really gave me chills.

35
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:52,316
You see, Ms. Han…

36
00:03:54,026 --> 00:03:57,696
[Seol-ah] <i>You think I killed my fiancé</i>
<i>for just 140,000?</i>

37
00:03:58,364 --> 00:04:00,658
Do you know what all insurance scammers
have in common?

38
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:03,494
Once they get a taste of money,
they want more.

39
00:04:04,203 --> 00:04:05,871
What is it that you really want to know?

40
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,290
Your fiancé

41
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:10,751
and Kim Yun-ji…

42
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,253
Did you kill them?

43
00:04:16,215 --> 00:04:17,466
<i>Even if no one else knows,</i>

44
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:19,677
<i>you know the truth.</i>

45
00:04:35,526 --> 00:04:36,527
{\an8}EPISODE 6

46
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,737
{\an8}[Mr. Koo] Detective experience
comes in handy in situations like this.

47
00:04:38,821 --> 00:04:42,157
{\an8}When the back of your neck tingles,
there is always a reason.

48
00:04:43,242 --> 00:04:45,077
{\an8}Big data proves it.

49
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:51,375
{\an8}What's the problem now, huh?

50
00:04:52,584 --> 00:04:55,587
{\an8}Hey, you should be excited
about finding new evidence.

51
00:04:56,547 --> 00:04:58,507
{\an8}Has big data ever steered you wrong?

52
00:05:00,843 --> 00:05:02,386
{\an8}Or ever wished it was wrong?

53
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,263
{\an8}What?

54
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:08,308
{\an8}You're kidding.
You still believe that woman?

55
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:13,522
{\an8}[stammers] This is insane.

56
00:05:30,706 --> 00:05:31,707
But…

57
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:37,046
back then, why did you stay by my side?

58
00:05:38,756 --> 00:05:39,757
When I was young,

59
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:42,926
no one wanted to be near me.
They said I reeked of smoke.

60
00:05:44,053 --> 00:05:47,514
So I'd go to the cafeteria alone
and you were always there waiting for me.

61
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:52,186
You'd sit across from me
and you would always eat with me.

62
00:05:53,145 --> 00:05:54,146
Remember?

63
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:56,523
Day after day…

64
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:01,111
That's what actually gave me
the courage to go to school.

65
00:06:03,155 --> 00:06:05,032
It wasn't our fault, you know.

66
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:10,037
I think that was the day it all started.

67
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:13,874
- [thuds]
- [parent] Hey! Find your mother.

68
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:17,544
I said go, find her. You little brat. Go!

69
00:06:18,295 --> 00:06:21,381
She's been running around
saying she's busy with her sales job,

70
00:06:21,465 --> 00:06:24,134
and just ditches her husband
like some dog poop.

71
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,428
You're just like your mother,

72
00:06:26,512 --> 00:06:28,347
you ungrateful little brat.

73
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,224
You little bastard.

74
00:06:30,307 --> 00:06:32,184
- Get over here.
- [Eun-hye whimpering]

75
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:34,019
Get over here.

76
00:06:34,103 --> 00:06:35,062
[grunts]

77
00:06:37,481 --> 00:06:38,816
Eun-hye, run.

78
00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:41,151
- Get back here!
- Eun-hye, run.

79
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:42,236
Get back!

80
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:49,743
You little…

81
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:51,995
Damn you!

82
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:54,248
- Goddamn you!
- [groaning]

83
00:06:55,332 --> 00:06:56,416
[sobbing]

84
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:07,511
[grunting, groaning]

85
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:14,017
Get up, Do Eun-hyuk.

86
00:07:41,003 --> 00:07:42,004
Here, try this.

87
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:44,631
Slow down, slow down.

88
00:07:48,385 --> 00:07:49,386
Here.

89
00:07:51,597 --> 00:07:53,056
You're eating so well.

90
00:07:59,771 --> 00:08:01,273
Come on, stay still.

91
00:08:10,032 --> 00:08:13,327
[Eun-hyuk] <i>That night,</i>
<i>I realized for the first time…</i>

92
00:08:15,245 --> 00:08:17,998
<i>what it really meant</i>
<i>to have someone by your side.</i>

93
00:08:20,417 --> 00:08:24,171
Even when I was beaten so badly,
it hurt less, and I could endure it.

94
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:26,548
I could keep going.

95
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:31,803
You know, no one gets to
pick their parents before they're born.

96
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:33,680
Not you, not me.

97
00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:37,100
So, it's not our fault.

98
00:08:38,227 --> 00:08:39,686
So, it's not my fault?

99
00:08:40,646 --> 00:08:43,565
The fire that day, that wasn't your fault.

100
00:08:49,863 --> 00:08:52,866
That guilt you feel for
being the only one who survived it's…

101
00:08:54,785 --> 00:08:56,036
time you let it go.

102
00:08:57,496 --> 00:08:58,622
[Suk-ji] Hey, stop.

103
00:09:04,211 --> 00:09:05,420
Stop drinking.

104
00:09:05,504 --> 00:09:08,215
Why do you guys always drink
on empty stomachs?

105
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:10,801
So, you don't mind
if the bar smells like food?

106
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,886
Who cares? It's my bar.

107
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:16,056
Mmm…

108
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:20,185
Maybe I should
just turn this place into a diner.

109
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:24,147
GANGHA POLICE STATION

110
00:09:30,988 --> 00:09:32,447
VIP INVITATION SPECIAL AUCTION

111
00:09:32,531 --> 00:09:35,284
We've been given the okay
to reinvestigate the Kim Yun-ji case.

112
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:37,411
[chuckles] Really?

113
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:38,912
Yes!

114
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:41,873
On the condition that I'll resign

115
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,459
if we mess up again this time.

116
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:50,465
Consider everyone
who was the auction house a suspect,

117
00:09:50,549 --> 00:09:53,260
and check each and every
one of them thoroughly, got it?

118
00:09:53,844 --> 00:09:57,264
[sighs] Then we'll have to
get our hands on the VIP list first.

119
00:09:57,806 --> 00:10:00,058
- There's someone who can help us.
- [line rings]

120
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:02,060
PORTRAITS OF A WOMAN: SPECIAL EXHIBITION

121
00:10:02,144 --> 00:10:04,146
This exhibition, Portrait of a Woman,

122
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:06,481
seeks to capture
the artistic spirit of female artists

123
00:10:06,565 --> 00:10:09,067
who confront the injustices of life

124
00:10:09,151 --> 00:10:11,361
and challenge convention
through their artistic work.

125
00:10:12,154 --> 00:10:14,406
This piece in particular
attempts to subvert

126
00:10:14,489 --> 00:10:16,867
the traditional image of the siren.

127
00:10:17,492 --> 00:10:21,246
Shedding the symbolism
of the witch who lures men to their deaths

128
00:10:21,330 --> 00:10:22,998
and instead portraying the femme fatale,

129
00:10:23,081 --> 00:10:26,335
a modern woman whose allure is undeniable,

130
00:10:26,418 --> 00:10:30,422
yet who never relinquishes her agency.

131
00:10:31,465 --> 00:10:33,508
That's exactly like you, Ms. Han.

132
00:10:35,427 --> 00:10:38,013
I'm glad to see you looking bright
after all you've been through.

133
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:41,475
I heard about your fiancé
and his accident.

134
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,101
That must have been really hard.

135
00:10:46,897 --> 00:10:49,066
Thank you very much for your concern.

136
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:51,360
If I had known,
I wouldn't have written about Ms. Kim.

137
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,446
Back to back funerals… [sighs]

138
00:11:01,536 --> 00:11:04,331
- Shall we wrap it up here, then?
- Sure, thank you.

139
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:05,999
You've suffered enough.

140
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:09,169
[Eun-hyuk sighs]

141
00:11:16,593 --> 00:11:18,929
Ms. Han didn't bite, not once.

142
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:20,722
I'm not surprised.

143
00:11:24,434 --> 00:11:25,852
Here you go.

144
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:30,899
Just give me the source,
and I'll turn it into a killer story.

145
00:11:30,982 --> 00:11:31,983
ANNUAL ADVERTISING CONTRACT

146
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,985
{\an8}THE CLIENT SHALL PAY THE SERVICE PROVIDER
A FEE OF 30,000,000 WON

147
00:11:34,069 --> 00:11:35,237
Wow.

148
00:11:35,946 --> 00:11:37,614
That's an expensive bill.

149
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:39,366
You got anything bigger?

150
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:40,700
Bigger?

151
00:11:40,784 --> 00:11:43,578
Gossip is only fun
when it's in the present tense.

152
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:46,957
Something bigger.

153
00:11:49,793 --> 00:11:50,877
Just wait a little.

154
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:24,369
Here's the insurance certificate
for the Stiller piece.

155
00:12:27,289 --> 00:12:29,583
These documents
hold a great deal of information.

156
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:33,295
Who, when and why

157
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:35,714
someone obtained the policy.

158
00:12:38,175 --> 00:12:41,344
With a nonexistent company
and hardly any evidence,

159
00:12:42,053 --> 00:12:43,305
is that why you confessed?

160
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:45,974
Let's face the truth.

161
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:49,144
You won't uncover anything at all.

162
00:12:50,353 --> 00:12:53,857
Because I'm the only one who knows
what happened.

163
00:12:56,359 --> 00:12:57,652
You wanted me to trust you…

164
00:13:00,864 --> 00:13:01,907
isn't that right?

165
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:19,549
[phone buzzes]

166
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:25,805
UNREAD MESSAGES

167
00:13:38,902 --> 00:13:40,320
[phone buzzing]

168
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,970
[Seol-ah] <i>Who are you?</i>

169
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:08,932
[mysterious voice] <i>Felix Storage.</i>
<i>45, Saebit road,</i>

170
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:11,643
<i>Yeonho district, Cheonin, Gyeonggi.</i>

171
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:16,439
<i>If you do not arrive within an hour,</i>
<i>your secret will be revealed to the world.</i>

172
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:52,035
[Seol-ah] I'm looking for this unit.

173
00:15:56,331 --> 00:15:57,332
[beeps]

174
00:16:05,632 --> 00:16:08,009
Is it possible to find out
who left this here?

175
00:16:08,093 --> 00:16:10,220
I cannot disclose that,
security regulations.

176
00:16:30,532 --> 00:16:33,326
Hello. Someone from Royal Auction
just went in, right?

177
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:34,577
I'm with her.

178
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:36,705
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU SENIOR MANAGER CHA WOO-SEOK

179
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:41,376
Thank you.

180
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,016
- [beeps]
- [door unlocks]

181
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:46,191
There are separate units for artwork
and wine in this high-security wing,

182
00:17:46,274 --> 00:17:48,318
so you can check them out later.

183
00:17:51,988 --> 00:17:53,698
This is the live security cam feed.

184
00:17:53,782 --> 00:17:58,578
You can monitor the entrance and interior
of our storage facility 24 hours a day.

185
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:47,293
[gasps]

186
00:19:05,854 --> 00:19:07,188
[panting]

187
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:15,196
No!

188
00:19:25,081 --> 00:19:26,916
[grunting]

189
00:19:28,751 --> 00:19:30,086
Are you okay?

190
00:19:36,926 --> 00:19:37,927
Oh, shit.

191
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:47,729
What…

192
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:07,957
All done now.

193
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,209
I'll give you some extra
hydrocolloid bandages.

194
00:20:10,293 --> 00:20:12,378
If it swells up,
just replace it with a new one.

195
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,213
Thank you very much.

196
00:20:15,298 --> 00:20:16,716
Does she need to go to the hospital?

197
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:18,843
It's just a superficial cut,

198
00:20:18,927 --> 00:20:21,638
if she takes good care of it,
it should heal without scarring.

199
00:20:27,143 --> 00:20:28,895
She used to be a nurse.

200
00:20:28,978 --> 00:20:31,689
She's an expert,
so you don't need to worry too much.

201
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:36,152
That's unusual for a secretary.

202
00:20:38,029 --> 00:20:39,530
I hired her on purpose.

203
00:20:39,614 --> 00:20:42,825
I'm still recovering from an accident.

204
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:04,389
[manager] We can't disclose the
owner's information due to privacy.

205
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:06,099
It's not an accident. It's an incident.

206
00:21:06,182 --> 00:21:07,558
Someone just got hurt here.

207
00:21:07,642 --> 00:21:09,394
Then call the police.

208
00:21:09,477 --> 00:21:10,937
If the police open an investigation,

209
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:13,314
won't other customers' ID's
be exposed too?

210
00:21:14,524 --> 00:21:17,443
If that's the case,
I'll have to rethink my contract.

211
00:21:17,527 --> 00:21:19,821
Gosh. Come on, sir.

212
00:21:19,904 --> 00:21:22,198
Seems like it would be a win-win
for both of you

213
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:25,410
if you just tell him who the
owner of that unit is.

214
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:27,704
[sighs]

215
00:21:29,247 --> 00:21:30,331
[sighs]

216
00:22:05,450 --> 00:22:06,951
Mr. Paek, may I ask you

217
00:22:08,578 --> 00:22:10,329
what brings you here at this hour?

218
00:22:11,539 --> 00:22:15,251
I was considering signing with them for
a warehouse I need for our new venture.

219
00:22:16,002 --> 00:22:17,712
And what about you two?

220
00:22:19,255 --> 00:22:21,841
[Seol-ah] We're here because the
auction house does business with them.

221
00:22:21,924 --> 00:22:24,343
Thank you for your help, Mr. Paek.

222
00:22:25,094 --> 00:22:27,597
Oh, you'll be all right? Let me drive you.

223
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:31,684
I'm fine, and I still have
some work to take care of.

224
00:22:32,935 --> 00:22:34,103
Then I can drive her.

225
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:36,689
So, could you just have your driver
bring her car?

226
00:22:39,734 --> 00:22:40,735
If you insist.

227
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:05,426
Were you following me?

228
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:06,594
Why did you come here?

229
00:23:07,428 --> 00:23:08,888
Why did you go into that warehouse?

230
00:23:09,514 --> 00:23:12,517
You think this is a coincidence?
Someone set a trap on purpose.

231
00:23:13,351 --> 00:23:15,186
I mean, why would you come here alone?

232
00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:17,814
[sighs] You should've told me first!

233
00:23:19,816 --> 00:23:23,361
Come on, tell me what's going on.
It's the only way that I can help you.

234
00:23:24,070 --> 00:23:25,071
Help me?

235
00:23:26,155 --> 00:23:27,490
So I'm not your suspect?

236
00:23:28,866 --> 00:23:30,743
What if I'm truly worried?

237
00:23:31,452 --> 00:23:33,371
You said you killed your parents,

238
00:23:34,163 --> 00:23:36,791
but I keep looking for reasons
it couldn't be you.

239
00:23:42,088 --> 00:23:44,507
- [key clicks]
- [Gong] Who's this one here?

240
00:23:45,591 --> 00:23:47,218
Oh, her name's Hwang Suk-ji.

241
00:23:47,301 --> 00:23:49,095
She's a friend of Ms. Han from school,

242
00:23:49,178 --> 00:23:51,305
and across the street
from the auction house.

243
00:23:52,890 --> 00:23:55,184
- What about her?
- Oh, that's Ko Sang-mi.

244
00:23:55,268 --> 00:23:56,686
Our assistant manager.

245
00:23:56,769 --> 00:23:59,939
This is the person Ms. Kim Yun-ji
was last seen with that day.

246
00:24:04,944 --> 00:24:07,530
Oh. [gasps] Ah…

247
00:24:07,613 --> 00:24:08,865
ROYAL AUCTION VIP NIGHT

248
00:24:08,948 --> 00:24:10,283
PAEK JUN-BEOM

249
00:24:10,366 --> 00:24:11,367
Here he is.

250
00:24:12,243 --> 00:24:13,703
Mr. Paek Jun-beom.

251
00:24:13,786 --> 00:24:15,997
He made a fortune with a start-up.

252
00:24:16,706 --> 00:24:20,084
Lately, he's been getting close
to Ms. Han.

253
00:24:25,006 --> 00:24:26,007
Not him.

254
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:30,469
I mean, why would a unicorn CEO
do something like that?

255
00:24:32,555 --> 00:24:35,474
Huh. There's something off about this guy.

256
00:24:40,396 --> 00:24:41,397
[Gong] Mr. Do Eun-hyuk?

257
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,857
Yeah.

258
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:45,193
Well, there's a lot of gossip at work.

259
00:24:45,276 --> 00:24:47,570
Apparently, he worships Ms. Han
like a queen.

260
00:24:48,404 --> 00:24:51,782
[sighs] Had I known they knew each other,
I wouldn't have hired him.

261
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:05,838
Do Eun-hyuk was in Cheongun
on the day of Yoon Seung-jae's death.

262
00:25:05,922 --> 00:25:08,257
And also at the scene
when Kim Yun-ji died.

263
00:25:08,341 --> 00:25:12,011
On top of that, he's the one
who vouched for Han Seol-ah's alibi.

264
00:25:13,471 --> 00:25:17,058
Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk
working together as accomplices?

265
00:25:19,268 --> 00:25:21,646
That sounds like a plausible theory.

266
00:25:21,729 --> 00:25:23,648
If there was an accomplice,

267
00:25:23,731 --> 00:25:27,360
we could dispute Han Seol-ah's alibi
for the time of Kim Yun-ji's fall.

268
00:25:27,443 --> 00:25:31,280
[sighs] It would be great if we had just
one case we could use to pressure him

269
00:25:31,364 --> 00:25:32,573
before calling him in as a witness.

270
00:25:32,657 --> 00:25:35,326
If we feel the Kim Yun-ji case
has reached a dead end,

271
00:25:35,409 --> 00:25:36,494
we can find another lead.

272
00:25:40,915 --> 00:25:43,542
Let's take another look at the
Yoon Seung-jae death first.

273
00:25:52,134 --> 00:25:55,596
I thought this person would show
themselves if I came alone.

274
00:25:58,266 --> 00:26:00,309
This isn't something you can handle alone.

275
00:26:00,393 --> 00:26:02,645
They lured you right into danger

276
00:26:03,729 --> 00:26:05,982
but then I showed up
and ruined their plan.

277
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:10,403
Do you think Mr. Paek
orchestrated all of this?

278
00:26:29,755 --> 00:26:31,674
There was a suspicious guy
in the warehouse.

279
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:35,261
Paek Jun-beom came running
as if he had been waiting.

280
00:26:40,641 --> 00:26:44,562
So, you think that he could be
watching us right now?

281
00:27:04,707 --> 00:27:06,709
[engine turns off]

282
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:15,301
[tires squeal]

283
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:29,690
Let's go in together.

284
00:27:31,525 --> 00:27:33,194
And let's see how they react.

285
00:28:04,392 --> 00:28:05,393
[door closes]

286
00:28:06,102 --> 00:28:07,353
[device beeps]

287
00:28:12,983 --> 00:28:16,320
[Seol-ah] In this house, there's only
water and alcohol. Take your pick.

288
00:28:19,615 --> 00:28:20,616
Same as you.

289
00:28:32,545 --> 00:28:34,547
[liquid pouring]

290
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:45,266
[Woo-seok] <i>I noticed the logo</i>
<i>on the business card.</i>

291
00:28:45,349 --> 00:28:46,600
<i>Does it mean anything?</i>

292
00:28:47,101 --> 00:28:50,479
[Jun-beom] <i>Anyway, that's sad.</i>
<i>You have trouble trusting people.</i>

293
00:28:56,193 --> 00:28:59,280
Is this wine easy to find?

294
00:29:02,158 --> 00:29:03,159
No.

295
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:05,870
It was his own private label actually.

296
00:29:05,953 --> 00:29:07,872
He only sold it at that restaurant.

297
00:29:08,873 --> 00:29:10,958
I saw the same wine
at Paek Jun-beom's place,

298
00:29:11,542 --> 00:29:13,419
so it's clear he's been
to that restaurant then.

299
00:29:39,028 --> 00:29:40,154
Aren't you afraid of me?

300
00:29:42,573 --> 00:29:44,366
It's possible that I did kill those men.

301
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:47,912
And that I'm just lying about it all.

302
00:29:52,416 --> 00:29:53,584
Well, that's possible.

303
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:58,005
I told you I was the one
who started the fire.

304
00:29:59,757 --> 00:30:00,925
Those words stuck with me…

305
00:30:02,593 --> 00:30:03,761
and sounded different.

306
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:09,141
As if you were asking me

307
00:30:10,684 --> 00:30:11,936
to uncover the truth.

308
00:30:18,776 --> 00:30:23,113
Usually, it's the adults
who create tragedies.

309
00:30:29,954 --> 00:30:31,288
It was my choice.

310
00:30:34,625 --> 00:30:36,460
- [clattering]
- [parent groaning]

311
00:30:43,467 --> 00:30:45,886
[Seol-ah] <i>Those who've</i>
<i>hit rock bottom know</i>

312
00:30:47,054 --> 00:30:51,934
<i>that misfortune tends to fall hardest</i>
<i>on those who have nothing.</i>

313
00:30:52,643 --> 00:30:55,771
<i>My father's debts</i>
<i>to loan sharks snowballed</i>

314
00:30:56,355 --> 00:30:58,148
<i>and there was no way out</i>

315
00:30:59,441 --> 00:31:00,693
<i>at least not until we died.</i>

316
00:31:02,528 --> 00:31:03,696
[parent 2] Go watch a movie.

317
00:31:05,197 --> 00:31:06,824
You said you wanted to see a movie.

318
00:31:08,284 --> 00:31:09,285
[chuckles]

319
00:31:11,245 --> 00:31:12,288
Go on.

320
00:31:15,457 --> 00:31:19,670
[Seol-ah] <i>One day, my mom told me</i>
<i>to go to the theater and watch a movie.</i>

321
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:25,843
<i>Something felt off.</i>

322
00:31:25,926 --> 00:31:27,136
DUMARI CHICKEN

323
00:31:29,346 --> 00:31:31,682
<i>So, instead of going to the movies,</i>

324
00:31:31,765 --> 00:31:33,684
<i>I bought fried chicken</i>
<i>and headed back home.</i>

325
00:31:35,311 --> 00:31:36,812
<i>When I got home,</i>

326
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:39,148
<i>my parents had already</i>
<i>swallowed pesticide…</i>

327
00:31:39,648 --> 00:31:41,025
Seol-ah.

328
00:31:42,693 --> 00:31:44,528
<i>…and they poured gasoline everywhere.</i>

329
00:31:48,365 --> 00:31:51,452
<i>I realized they had planned</i>
<i>to make it look like an accident.</i>

330
00:32:17,853 --> 00:32:19,897
I was going to die with them too…

331
00:32:23,692 --> 00:32:25,069
but I didn't.

332
00:32:29,990 --> 00:32:31,992
[crying]

333
00:32:33,035 --> 00:32:36,622
<i>Just like that,</i>
<i>I was left all alone in hell.</i>

334
00:32:44,380 --> 00:32:45,631
Later, I found out

335
00:32:46,715 --> 00:32:48,676
that my father
planned to pay off his debts…

336
00:32:50,594 --> 00:32:52,638
with the life insurance money.

337
00:32:54,431 --> 00:32:58,435
When my mom found out about his plan,
she decided to die with him.

338
00:32:59,812 --> 00:33:01,397
And it's at the cost of their lives

339
00:33:03,148 --> 00:33:04,900
that I am alive today.

340
00:33:09,196 --> 00:33:10,656
I'm a terrible daughter.

341
00:33:12,366 --> 00:33:15,327
At that moment, you must have
wanted to ease your parents' suffering.

342
00:33:16,245 --> 00:33:20,999
The world was so cruel
that even a child wanted to end her life.

343
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:34,138
[sighs]

344
00:33:57,369 --> 00:33:58,370
Don't hold back.

345
00:34:02,207 --> 00:34:03,333
It's okay to cry.

346
00:34:27,483 --> 00:34:30,027
GANGHA POLICE STATION

347
00:34:33,238 --> 00:34:34,656
The cause of death is drowning,

348
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:36,867
and the injuries appear to have
occurred after entering the water.

349
00:34:36,950 --> 00:34:38,118
YACHT REPAIRED THE DAY BEFORE THE ACCIDENT

350
00:34:38,202 --> 00:34:41,580
There's record of the yacht being repaired
the day before the accident.

351
00:34:41,663 --> 00:34:43,582
Yes, Cheongun Police
checked with the company

352
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:45,709
and they said
there were no particular issues.

353
00:34:47,836 --> 00:34:49,213
The scene could say otherwise.

354
00:34:49,713 --> 00:34:50,714
Let's go take a look.

355
00:34:53,717 --> 00:34:54,718
Hello.

356
00:34:56,303 --> 00:34:57,471
Uh, Sang-mi.

357
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:01,433
You're in charge of our external
storage providers, is that correct?

358
00:35:01,517 --> 00:35:02,643
Yes.

359
00:35:02,726 --> 00:35:05,187
Send me that list right away please.

360
00:35:05,270 --> 00:35:06,980
Sure, I'll send it over now.

361
00:35:12,361 --> 00:35:15,197
OFF-SITE STORAGE PROVIDER CONTRACT STATUS

362
00:35:23,372 --> 00:35:24,414
[voice] <i>Within an hour.</i>

363
00:35:31,672 --> 00:35:33,006
[knocks on door]

364
00:35:33,090 --> 00:35:34,967
Do you need to contact
one of the companies?

365
00:35:36,677 --> 00:35:37,845
Uh.

366
00:35:37,928 --> 00:35:42,558
Can you tell me which pieces are stored
at a warehouse called Felix Storage?

367
00:35:42,641 --> 00:35:45,978
That warehouse has been reserved
for Chair Kim's personal use.

368
00:35:46,061 --> 00:35:48,772
Even though there's a contract, I'm pretty
sure nothing has been stored there yet.

369
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:51,400
Really?

370
00:35:51,483 --> 00:35:53,443
At least officially.
No orders have been given.

371
00:35:54,194 --> 00:35:55,404
All right.

372
00:36:04,037 --> 00:36:06,039
[opera music playing]

373
00:36:20,846 --> 00:36:22,222
Hmm, hey. You're here.

374
00:36:23,223 --> 00:36:24,725
Is it going to Hannam-dong?

375
00:36:25,517 --> 00:36:26,602
Mm-hmm.

376
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:30,439
She spent 2.1 million
on those random paintings,

377
00:36:30,522 --> 00:36:32,774
she must be waiting
with her neck stretched out.

378
00:36:32,858 --> 00:36:35,152
It's about time I sent the invitation.

379
00:36:36,695 --> 00:36:38,780
Once that lady receives your kimchi jar,

380
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:42,075
she will finally be able to
buy the paintings she really wants.

381
00:36:42,159 --> 00:36:43,160
Mm-hmm.

382
00:36:43,911 --> 00:36:47,789
Even with luxury brands,
you have to spend thousands

383
00:36:47,873 --> 00:36:49,917
just to get that bag, you know?

384
00:36:52,336 --> 00:36:55,714
They're so full of themselves,
thinking they've been chosen.

385
00:36:55,797 --> 00:36:58,967
They'll throw their own money around
and still not come to their senses.

386
00:37:03,263 --> 00:37:06,558
How did you know you'd get
2.1 million dollars from Hannam-dong?

387
00:37:08,769 --> 00:37:10,687
You need to look at their eyes.

388
00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:14,232
Greed shows itself. They can't hide it.

389
00:37:22,282 --> 00:37:25,077
I see it sometimes too. Those eyes.

390
00:37:26,787 --> 00:37:27,788
Hmm.

391
00:37:28,914 --> 00:37:30,624
Seriously, what is this thing?

392
00:37:31,375 --> 00:37:33,502
They're that desperate to get it?

393
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:34,586
Good grief.

394
00:37:51,103 --> 00:37:55,273
Oh, and I've emailed you the media art
video for our next exhibition.

395
00:37:55,357 --> 00:37:57,150
- Please take a look.
- Hmm.

396
00:37:57,651 --> 00:37:58,735
Did it turn out well?

397
00:37:58,819 --> 00:38:01,363
Nothing really catches my eye these days.

398
00:38:01,947 --> 00:38:04,408
The artist reinterprets
Andy Warhol's work,

399
00:38:04,491 --> 00:38:06,451
showing the boldness
of an emerging artist.

400
00:38:06,535 --> 00:38:09,705
It's a bit provocative,
but aligns well with current trends.

401
00:38:11,873 --> 00:38:12,958
Hmm, that right?

402
00:38:21,925 --> 00:38:22,926
INBOX

403
00:38:23,010 --> 00:38:24,011
Let's see.

404
00:38:26,555 --> 00:38:27,723
Mmm.

405
00:38:29,057 --> 00:38:30,892
I like the colors in it.

406
00:38:32,853 --> 00:38:35,022
The cuts feel a bit fast I think.

407
00:38:36,606 --> 00:38:39,651
Kids these days
have such interesting ideas, huh?

408
00:38:40,986 --> 00:38:41,987
I'm glad to hear that.

409
00:38:42,070 --> 00:38:44,698
Then we'll refine it a bit more
based on your feedback.

410
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:46,116
All right.

411
00:39:17,064 --> 00:39:18,273
[Eun-hye] <i>Who is it?</i>

412
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:19,900
I'm here from the auction house.

413
00:39:40,879 --> 00:39:42,005
[boater] <i>The</i> Katarina?

414
00:39:42,798 --> 00:39:44,591
It had a few minor issues but…

415
00:39:45,842 --> 00:39:47,636
the thing with yachts is

416
00:39:47,719 --> 00:39:49,930
they may look big but they're sensitive.

417
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:54,559
The <i>Katarina</i>. The <i>Katarina</i> was, uh…

418
00:39:54,643 --> 00:39:55,977
Yes. Here it is.

419
00:39:56,937 --> 00:39:58,396
BOAT MAINTENANCE ESTIMATE

420
00:40:00,273 --> 00:40:02,818
The connection between the engine
and starter was a bit loose.

421
00:40:03,443 --> 00:40:06,822
If you think of it in human terms,
it's like being on the verge of divorce.

422
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:09,324
The engine wouldn't start properly

423
00:40:09,407 --> 00:40:11,993
and sometimes it would
just cut out unexpectedly.

424
00:40:12,869 --> 00:40:14,663
- Well, then--
- You see,

425
00:40:15,372 --> 00:40:17,374
I made sure to fix all of that, you know?

426
00:40:19,167 --> 00:40:20,877
It had nothing to do with the yacht.

427
00:40:20,961 --> 00:40:22,754
Look, my pride is on the line here.

428
00:40:22,838 --> 00:40:24,673
I mean, you think I can't fix this?

429
00:40:24,756 --> 00:40:28,051
Well, then did Mr. Yoon Seung-jae
say anything that day?

430
00:40:28,135 --> 00:40:31,888
If I remember correctly,
his friend came instead.

431
00:40:32,472 --> 00:40:34,182
I think Mr. Yoon said he was busy.

432
00:40:35,183 --> 00:40:36,393
His friend?

433
00:40:38,103 --> 00:40:39,104
Was it a guy?

434
00:40:39,729 --> 00:40:42,691
Yeah, the both of them
used to come by my shop together.

435
00:40:47,654 --> 00:40:48,780
Is this him?

436
00:40:52,117 --> 00:40:53,118
[boater] Was it him?

437
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:55,537
Looking at his face, I think it was him.

438
00:40:56,454 --> 00:40:57,789
Yeah.

439
00:41:01,001 --> 00:41:03,420
So, can you do the repairs
even if the owner isn't there?

440
00:41:04,296 --> 00:41:07,382
Well, I was able to do it
because that guy had the keys.

441
00:41:08,133 --> 00:41:09,509
The keys?

442
00:41:09,593 --> 00:41:12,179
The keys for the yacht. The <i>Katarina.</i>

443
00:41:25,984 --> 00:41:27,110
You're leaving early?

444
00:41:27,194 --> 00:41:29,362
That's why I told you
not to come in today.

445
00:41:30,405 --> 00:41:32,532
Take this and get some sleep, okay?

446
00:41:33,617 --> 00:41:35,410
Or you wanna go to the hospital?
Want me to come?

447
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:37,120
I don't have time. I need to hurry.

448
00:41:37,204 --> 00:41:39,748
Where are you going?
I thought you were going home.

449
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:42,083
There's a problem
with the catalog we sent over.

450
00:41:42,167 --> 00:41:43,960
I need to stop by the print shop.

451
00:41:44,044 --> 00:41:45,670
But that's the Auction Team…

452
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:48,381
Han Seol-ah told you to do it?

453
00:41:48,465 --> 00:41:50,008
That Auction Team's busy, so…

454
00:41:50,091 --> 00:41:51,676
Brother, are you an idiot?

455
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:53,470
Why do her words leave you frozen?

456
00:41:53,553 --> 00:41:55,555
The catalog has my photos. It's fine.

457
00:41:56,765 --> 00:41:59,559
I'll stop by the print shop
and then head home, all right?

458
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:03,355
[Eun-hyuk coughing]

459
00:42:53,989 --> 00:42:58,285
At the next major auction, one of you two
will be standing next to me.

460
00:42:58,368 --> 00:43:01,997
I've let them know that the associate
auctioneer will be chosen internally,

461
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:03,498
so give it your best.

462
00:43:04,082 --> 00:43:05,125
- Will do.
- Will do.

463
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:15,593
You can go.

464
00:43:32,944 --> 00:43:33,945
Lunch?

465
00:43:34,029 --> 00:43:35,447
Did you eat?

466
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:36,865
[chuckles] Not yet.

467
00:43:38,033 --> 00:43:39,034
Then shall we go eat?

468
00:43:51,046 --> 00:43:53,173
[Na-hee] <i>I'm telling you,</i>
<i>it's really suspicious.</i>

469
00:43:53,256 --> 00:43:58,094
Come on. What, that… Are you suggesting
they've got a thing going on?

470
00:43:58,178 --> 00:43:59,387
Ms. Han? No way.

471
00:43:59,471 --> 00:44:00,972
It's in their eyes.

472
00:44:01,056 --> 00:44:02,724
Their eyes were full of romance.

473
00:44:02,807 --> 00:44:04,934
They even went out for lunch on their own.

474
00:44:05,018 --> 00:44:07,520
Oh, my. Could they already be dating?

475
00:44:08,563 --> 00:44:10,398
Hey. Only for yourself?

476
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:13,818
I was saving this.

477
00:44:17,197 --> 00:44:18,823
Yeah? Here.

478
00:44:18,907 --> 00:44:20,658
As usual, this gets me through the day.

479
00:44:34,464 --> 00:44:35,965
This one's on the house.

480
00:44:36,049 --> 00:44:37,967
They say fighting brings people closer.

481
00:44:38,051 --> 00:44:39,928
It's nice to see you two getting along.

482
00:44:40,011 --> 00:44:42,764
- [chuckles]
- Thanks. We need to talk about something.

483
00:44:42,847 --> 00:44:44,265
Oh, sure.

484
00:44:59,239 --> 00:45:02,200
By tomorrow, even the cleaning lady
at the auction house

485
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:03,785
will be able to recognize you

486
00:45:04,786 --> 00:45:06,121
as the subject of all the gossip.

487
00:45:06,704 --> 00:45:07,705
What? No way.

488
00:45:12,836 --> 00:45:14,796
Hey. Come on. Come on.

489
00:45:16,381 --> 00:45:17,382
[chuckles]

490
00:45:20,635 --> 00:45:22,011
That'll do the trick.

491
00:45:25,348 --> 00:45:26,516
Tell me everything.

492
00:45:27,183 --> 00:45:29,686
Anything that could be connected
to Paek Jun-beom.

493
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:35,650
I met him roughly a week
before Yun-ji's accident.

494
00:45:36,192 --> 00:45:38,111
It was at the preview exhibition.

495
00:45:39,112 --> 00:45:40,196
Are you sure?

496
00:45:40,780 --> 00:45:43,324
Yes. I had never met him before then.

497
00:45:46,870 --> 00:45:48,121
But,

498
00:45:48,788 --> 00:45:50,957
for some reason, it felt like he knew me.

499
00:45:51,833 --> 00:45:53,418
I can't explain it,

500
00:45:55,170 --> 00:45:57,213
but it was like he could see through me.

501
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:01,342
It's very likely that he already knew you.

502
00:46:02,093 --> 00:46:05,305
I bet he'd been watching you
and approached deliberately.

503
00:46:07,348 --> 00:46:08,475
Why would that be?

504
00:46:10,727 --> 00:46:11,728
[sighs]

505
00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:14,606
If he's the one who killed those men,

506
00:46:15,231 --> 00:46:16,566
there's only one answer.

507
00:46:20,445 --> 00:46:21,613
He wants Han Seol-ah.

508
00:47:02,487 --> 00:47:04,489
HAN SEOL-AH(28).M4A

509
00:47:04,572 --> 00:47:05,573
[Eun-hyuk] <i>Seol-ah.</i>

510
00:47:06,449 --> 00:47:07,450
<i>Where are you?</i>

511
00:47:08,409 --> 00:47:09,410
<i>Why?</i>

512
00:47:10,537 --> 00:47:11,538
<i>Seung-jae…</i>

513
00:47:12,956 --> 00:47:14,123
<i>He was in an accident.</i>

514
00:47:15,083 --> 00:47:16,584
<i>Uh, can you…</i>

515
00:47:17,627 --> 00:47:19,254
<i>Can you come to the harbor right away?</i>

516
00:47:22,590 --> 00:47:24,551
"Come to the harbor right away?"

517
00:47:25,134 --> 00:47:26,386
According to the report,

518
00:47:26,469 --> 00:47:28,596
Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk
showed up at the scene

519
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:30,515
less than an hour
after the police called them.

520
00:47:31,224 --> 00:47:34,602
By the way,
why wasn't that on the list of evidence?

521
00:47:36,271 --> 00:47:38,022
I just discovered it a little late.

522
00:47:38,106 --> 00:47:39,607
Well, did you report it?

523
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:41,526
Of course.

524
00:47:46,948 --> 00:47:47,949
YOUR HOME

525
00:47:48,032 --> 00:47:49,033
[Eun-gyeom] See.

526
00:47:49,659 --> 00:47:52,328
This is normally
where the CEO's photo goes,

527
00:47:52,412 --> 00:47:53,997
and there isn't one.

528
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:56,874
So, this jerk must be insecure
about his looks, right?

529
00:47:56,958 --> 00:47:57,959
But get this.

530
00:48:00,712 --> 00:48:02,505
Totally blew my expectations.

531
00:48:03,131 --> 00:48:05,675
He's seriously handsome.

532
00:48:05,758 --> 00:48:08,803
I mean, really. He's unreal, you know?
Handsome, tall, smart,

533
00:48:08,886 --> 00:48:10,972
built a killer app and ends up super rich.

534
00:48:12,348 --> 00:48:13,558
Why didn't you make one too?

535
00:48:13,641 --> 00:48:14,559
I know, right?

536
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:16,853
Why does my brain
only work well on bad stuff?

537
00:48:16,936 --> 00:48:17,812
Hey, zoom in a bit.

538
00:48:17,895 --> 00:48:19,397
PAEK JUN-BEOM08.JPG

539
00:48:19,480 --> 00:48:21,107
- Which one?
- This one.

540
00:48:21,190 --> 00:48:22,483
- This?
- Yeah.

541
00:48:28,156 --> 00:48:29,157
"OnWorld"?

542
00:48:29,657 --> 00:48:31,451
[newsreader] <i>On the 14th,</i>
<i>amid a terrorist attack</i>

543
00:48:31,534 --> 00:48:33,161
<i>by the IS armed group in Raqqa, Syria,</i>

544
00:48:33,244 --> 00:48:36,164
<i>a Korean aid worker was killed,</i>
<i>adding to the tragedy.</i>

545
00:48:36,247 --> 00:48:39,542
<i>It took place in an area controlled</i>
<i>by IS civilian forces.</i>

546
00:48:40,126 --> 00:48:42,503
Lee Su-ho died there while with OnWorld.

547
00:48:59,187 --> 00:49:00,855
{\an8}ONWORLD VOLUNTEER WORK PHOTO BOOK

548
00:49:06,277 --> 00:49:07,612
[staff] Sorry to keep you waiting.

549
00:49:07,695 --> 00:49:11,491
[chuckles] It took me a little while
to find it.

550
00:49:11,574 --> 00:49:13,451
- That's all right.
- Please have a seat.

551
00:49:18,081 --> 00:49:21,876
Well, there's no record of anyone
named Paek Jun-beom in the staff logs,

552
00:49:21,959 --> 00:49:25,963
but if he was wearing one of our vests,
he was probably a volunteer.

553
00:49:26,964 --> 00:49:28,675
- A volunteer you say?
- Yes.

554
00:49:28,758 --> 00:49:31,678
There are so many and most of them
only do it as a one-off.

555
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:34,097
Oh, I can ask
the volunteer group about him.

556
00:49:35,098 --> 00:49:36,099
Okay.

557
00:49:36,182 --> 00:49:41,813
And Mr. Lee Su-ho was indeed
one of our staff members here.

558
00:49:44,190 --> 00:49:46,567
I heard there was an incident in Syria,

559
00:49:46,651 --> 00:49:49,404
but it happened
before I joined the organization.

560
00:49:49,904 --> 00:49:52,532
Is there anyone still around
who knew him well?

561
00:49:52,615 --> 00:49:57,745
Hmm, Manager Lee Kwang-jin from the
relief team probably knew him well.

562
00:49:57,829 --> 00:49:59,997
He's been on all the overseas missions.

563
00:50:01,082 --> 00:50:03,418
Then he might remember
Paek Jun-beom as well.

564
00:50:03,501 --> 00:50:05,878
Well, if they went together, yes.

565
00:50:05,962 --> 00:50:07,171
Is he here now?

566
00:50:07,255 --> 00:50:11,384
Ah, he left on a work trip to Laos,
but he'll be back soon.

567
00:50:16,723 --> 00:50:19,100
PERSONNEL FILE
NAME: LEE SU-HO

568
00:50:25,106 --> 00:50:26,107
Yes. Up here.

569
00:50:28,276 --> 00:50:29,944
We're looking for accomplices

570
00:50:30,027 --> 00:50:33,656
and trying to identify suspects
among people close to Han Seol-ah.

571
00:50:34,282 --> 00:50:37,160
I'm here today
to ask for your cooperation.

572
00:50:37,243 --> 00:50:39,495
Detective Gong, it's your request.

573
00:50:40,163 --> 00:50:42,290
Of course I can hand over
her parents' files.

574
00:50:42,915 --> 00:50:43,916
What else do you need?

575
00:50:46,085 --> 00:50:50,089
For the time being, SIU should stay put
and leave everything to the police.

576
00:50:54,218 --> 00:50:55,636
Gosh, where have you been?

577
00:50:56,220 --> 00:50:58,306
- Why?
- Detective Gong is here.

578
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:00,057
Over there.

579
00:51:04,353 --> 00:51:06,397
We'll ask you to join the investigation

580
00:51:06,481 --> 00:51:08,232
once we apprehend Kim Yun-ji's killer.

581
00:51:09,692 --> 00:51:11,778
Well, sure. That's fine by us.

582
00:51:19,702 --> 00:51:21,287
Why are you doing all this?

583
00:51:24,207 --> 00:51:26,667
Do you even know what I had to do
to cover up the spy phone?

584
00:51:29,378 --> 00:51:31,339
Do you really trust Han Seol-ah?

585
00:51:31,422 --> 00:51:33,758
She even collected
her parents' insurance money.

586
00:51:33,841 --> 00:51:35,426
It was a family suicide.

587
00:51:35,510 --> 00:51:38,346
Her family tried to die together,
and only Han Seol-ah survived.

588
00:51:38,930 --> 00:51:41,265
She went through that at only 15.

589
00:51:45,603 --> 00:51:48,773
She is just a victim here.

590
00:51:49,273 --> 00:51:52,735
Are you sure you're not letting your
emotions keep you from seeing the truth?

591
00:52:39,532 --> 00:52:40,533
Syria…

592
00:52:50,376 --> 00:52:52,378
[paper rustling]

593
00:53:01,721 --> 00:53:03,806
BOAT MAINTENANCE ESTIMATE

594
00:53:04,390 --> 00:53:05,391
This?

595
00:53:07,143 --> 00:53:08,477
Seol-ah asked me to.

596
00:53:09,687 --> 00:53:12,231
She was worried because the yacht
wouldn't start properly,

597
00:53:12,982 --> 00:53:15,192
and since Seung-jae was too busy
to deal with it…

598
00:53:17,194 --> 00:53:18,696
she asked me to get it fixed.

599
00:53:19,780 --> 00:53:21,407
I called the mechanic and it was repaired.

600
00:53:21,490 --> 00:53:23,367
And the accident happened
the next day, right?

601
00:53:25,578 --> 00:53:26,662
Who gave you the keys?

602
00:53:28,998 --> 00:53:29,999
Seol-ah.

603
00:53:32,543 --> 00:53:35,004
If it were me, I probably
wouldn't have done that favor.

604
00:53:36,505 --> 00:53:37,506
Mr. Do Eun-hyuk.

605
00:53:38,215 --> 00:53:42,136
It seems like Han Seol-ah
comes first in everything you do, huh?

606
00:53:45,056 --> 00:53:47,058
[phone buzzing]

607
00:53:50,728 --> 00:53:52,229
SEOL-AH

608
00:53:55,107 --> 00:53:56,984
Go ahead and answer it. It's okay.

609
00:54:02,114 --> 00:54:03,115
[sighs]

610
00:54:07,328 --> 00:54:09,080
SEOL-AH

611
00:54:16,796 --> 00:54:17,797
Why? Is there a problem?

612
00:54:19,507 --> 00:54:20,675
No.

613
00:54:21,801 --> 00:54:22,802
There isn't.

614
00:54:30,768 --> 00:54:32,728
MISSED CALL
SEOL-AH

615
00:54:35,272 --> 00:54:39,694
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

616
00:54:40,778 --> 00:54:43,155
<i>I'm Lee Kwang-jin,</i>
<i>manager of OnWorld's relief team.</i>

617
00:54:43,739 --> 00:54:45,491
<i>I hear you were asking for me.</i>

618
00:54:45,574 --> 00:54:46,701
Oh, yeah. Hello.

619
00:54:47,201 --> 00:54:49,578
Um, I'm investigating
Mr. Lee Su-ho's acci--

620
00:54:49,662 --> 00:54:53,165
<i>Su-ho's death. It's all because of</i>
<i>that woman, Han Seol-ah.</i>

621
00:54:55,543 --> 00:54:57,461
<i>I'm getting on a flight</i>
<i>to Korea right now.</i>

622
00:54:57,545 --> 00:54:59,630
<i>I'll tell you everything when I arrive.</i>

623
00:55:36,375 --> 00:55:37,376
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin?

624
00:55:38,878 --> 00:55:39,920
Yes.

625
00:55:42,757 --> 00:55:44,216
We spoke on the phone earlier.

626
00:56:33,099 --> 00:56:34,100
[Kwang-jin] Yes, of course.

627
00:56:34,850 --> 00:56:36,143
I remember Jun-beom.

628
00:56:37,228 --> 00:56:40,147
He started volunteering with OnWorld
back in college.

629
00:56:41,273 --> 00:56:43,192
Even though his family
was pretty well-off.

630
00:56:43,275 --> 00:56:46,112
he was interested
in helping people in need.

631
00:56:46,195 --> 00:56:47,988
Did he do volunteer work?

632
00:56:48,489 --> 00:56:49,490
Yes.

633
00:56:49,573 --> 00:56:52,034
He even took a break from school to do it.

634
00:57:00,292 --> 00:57:02,920
[scoffs] If only that hadn't happened
in Syria…

635
00:57:04,046 --> 00:57:05,047
Syria?

636
00:57:06,173 --> 00:57:08,008
So, he was there with Lee Su-ho?

637
00:57:11,887 --> 00:57:13,681
[both exclaim]

638
00:57:55,222 --> 00:57:56,348
[groans]

639
01:00:00,389 --> 01:00:03,851
{\an8}Is there anything you remember at all?

640
01:00:03,934 --> 01:00:04,935
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>It was my fault.</i>

641
01:00:05,019 --> 01:00:06,520
{\an8}<i>What if there's another accomplice?</i>

642
01:00:07,146 --> 01:00:09,940
{\an8}Someone with money, time,
and the ability to pull it off.

643
01:00:10,024 --> 01:00:11,150
{\an8}I've seen him before.

644
01:00:11,233 --> 01:00:12,568
{\an8}YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

645
01:00:12,651 --> 01:00:13,777
{\an8}[Chair Kim] <i>If you've lost everything,</i>

646
01:00:13,861 --> 01:00:17,656
{\an8}you have nothing left to lose
and nothing left to fear either.

647
01:00:17,740 --> 01:00:21,910
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>The accident happened</i>
<i>while tracking the suspect.</i>

648
01:00:21,994 --> 01:00:24,121
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>What if ended up</i>
<i>just using you and ditching you?</i>

649
01:00:24,204 --> 01:00:25,456
{\an8}I don't care.

650
01:00:27,249 --> 01:00:28,959
{\an8}<i>You can just use me.</i>

